      "text": "BORDER BANDITS CAUGHT! On January 23, U.S. Border Patrol agents responded to reports of gunfire along the southern border near Tecate. At the request of the Foreign Operations Division, an AMO ASTAR crew was dispatched and arrived on scene, providing critical aerial surveillance and assistance. The Government of Mexico also deployed military and law enforcement personnel to the area along the Mexican side.  \n  \nThe aircrew observed several armed individuals on the Mexican side, and a drone operated by the suspects was detected in the vicinity. While providing critical overwatch, U.S. Border Patrol safely apprehended one individual running northbound, away from the gunfire, while Mexican authorities detained three armed suspects and recovered abandoned AK-47 magazines. The area was secured through close coordination between U.S. and Mexican officials, with our aircrew providing aerial surveillance on station until the situation was declared safe. Great international collaboration and partnerships along the border to apprehend these bandits! #BorderSecurity",
      "text_resolved": "BORDER BANDITS CAUGHT! On January 23, U.S. Border Patrol agents responded to reports of gunfire along the southern border near Tecate. At the request of the Foreign Operations Division, an AMO ASTAR crew was dispatched and arrived on scene, providing critical aerial surveillance and assistance. The Government of Mexico also deployed military and law enforcement personnel to the area along the Mexican side.  \n  \nThe aircrew observed several armed individuals on the Mexican side, and a drone operated by the suspects was detected in the vicinity. While providing critical overwatch, U.S. Border Patrol safely apprehended one individual running northbound, away from the gunfire, while Mexican authorities detained three armed suspects and recovered abandoned AK-47 magazines. The area was secured through close coordination between U.S. and Mexican officials, with our aircrew providing aerial surveillance on station until the situation was declared safe. Great international collaboration and partnerships along the border to apprehend these bandits! #BorderSecurity",
